SIMPLE: rotative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rotative
<hw>Ro"ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>rotatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>turning, as a wheel; rotary;
rotational.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This high <qex>rotative</qex> velocity of the sun must cause an
equatorial rise of the solar atmosphere.</q>
<rj><qau>Siemens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rotative engine</b></col>, <cd>a steam engine in which
the reciprocating motion of the piston is transformed into a continuous
rotary motion, as by means of a connecting rod, a working beam and
crank, or an oscillating cylinder.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rotator</ent>⟦br⟧
